name: Andrejs Blakunovs
headline: Motion Designer | Student Life Enhancer | Musical Artist
creator: False
bio:
Originally from Latvia, I was always fond of sports. Therefore, my journey to professional world begins with 4-years Sport Management bachelor course at Coventry University. Being enchanted by the culture and vibrance of extracurricular life, I started working as Community Engagement Coordinator at the local Student Union. It gave me a fantastic view on student life, the processes and strategies to improve student life.

After my fixed contract expired, I worked as a Marketing Assistant at Parkwood Leisure and Community Centre Coordinator at Poole Communities Trust. All that gave me essential understanding of professional communication and management. But I always wanted to make a difference and return to working with student environment.

My last five years represent selfless dedication to student life at Innopolis University, where I worked as Student Activities Coordinator. I have implemented numerous projects with Student Affairs department and the Student Union. You can view the most outstanding projects via this youtube channel: https://www.youtube.com/@innopolisuniversitystudent2415

But I feel here's the time for the new challenge and learning something new that would sustain me for the next decade. I discovered the passion for motion design, so here I am to become a professional motion designer! Check out my showreel: https://vimeo.com/840573079

name: Tanwan Fabrice Mbachan
headline: Cybersecurity Architect | DevSecOps Specialist | Malware Analyst & Pentester | MSc in Security Engineering
creator: False
bio:
Pursuing a master's degree in Security and Network Engineering at Innopolis University, I am currently enhancing my expertise in computer engineering while actively working as a Penetration Tester at Positive Technologies. My core competencies lie in CTF, fuzzing, and utilizing tools like Burp Suite to ensure robust cybersecurity defenses.

In my recent role at Energetia, part of Innogeotech, our team integrated automated security testing into CI/CD pipelines and conducted thorough security assessments, leveraging my skills in vulnerability research and exploit development. Driven by a commitment to excellence, I aim to contribute to Positive Technologies by bringing a diverse perspective to security challenges and aligning with the organization's goals through proactive and strategic security practices.

name: Egor Tolmachev
headline: Senior NLP/CV/ML Engineer
creator: False
bio:
An accomplished Senior Machine Learning Engineer with a rich tapestry of experience spanning NeuralDeepTech, QuanyshAI, Docet TI, red_mad_robot, and Kobak Lab. Rooted in St. Petersburg but with a global footprint, I've embraced diverse roles from spearheading computer vision projects in Cyprus to remotely architecting state-of-the-art machine learning models in Russia.

At the heart of my journey lies a deep-seated expertise in neural networks, from fine-tuning LLMs to CV problems like Image Classification, Object Detection, Senamtic Segmentation and so on. I am also interested in deep integration of neural networks with hardware, working with non-standard data corpuses and solving problems at the intersection of high-tech spheres.

Beyond the code, I've successfully led teams, ensuring the smooth transition of projects from inception to deployment. My toolkit, brimming with tools like PyTorch, Elasticsearch, Docker, and ROS, underscores my holistic approach to machine learning and computer vision. Whether it's the calibration of LiDARs on embedded hardware, data mining from multiple sensors, or crafting smart video surveillance platforms, I'm trying to be at the forefront, turning visions into tangible solutions.

name: Alex Karavaev
headline: Software Engineer | ROS Germany
creator: True
bio:
One of my main goals in life is to build something that will be beneficial to humanity. I believe that building intelligent machines is the best way for me to achieve this goal. I find it exciting to take a machine and give it the ability to understand and interact with the world around it. As someone who has always been fascinated by science fiction and technology, I have always enjoyed the idea of building my own version of a C3-PO like in Star Wars.

In my professional life, I thrive in challenging and rapidly changing environments, particularly when working with cutting edge technology and collaborating with others towards a common goal. In my spare time, I enjoy developing open source software and reading books. I also have a small blog where I discuss topics related to technology, innovation, and the moral implications of technology development.

name: Stepan Rogonov
headline: Python developer at Self-employed
creator: False
bio:
Более 10 лет опыта разработки, из которых более 5 лет совокупного опыта индустриальной разработки. В прошлом активный участник олимпиадного программирования.

Непрерывно получаю высшее образование с 2012 года, в настоящее время являяюсь аспирантом Тверского Государственного Университета и тренером университетской команды по командному олимпиадному программированию.

Карьеру начинал разработчиком C++ . В последствии достиг должности ведущего Java разработчика. От имени университета принимал участие в индустриальном проекте в роли ведущего Python разработчика.

Являюсь активным пользователем Linux, даже на домашнем ПК. Имею степень магистра в области компьютерной безопасности, и использую только 20 символьные криптостойкие пароли. Неоднократно настраивал рабочее окружение, в том числе с переустановкой операционной системы и даже на удалённом сервере.

Параллельно с основной программой обучения закончил продвинутые курсы машинного обучения и анализа данных. Пожалел, что не выбрал университетскую программу с большим количеством часов математики (восполнял недостаток посещая индивидуального репетитора). В магистратуре защищал проект по кластеризации кошельков bitcoin на основе совершённых транзакций.

Я не считаю своей главной задачей найти работу или начать получать деньги. Я хочу своей работой делать жизнь других людей легче и прежде всего стремлюсь решать проблему, с которой ко мне обращаются, а не только лишь исполнять минимально необходимые требования ТЗ.

name: Emeka Nzeopara
headline: Security Engineer @ Wazuh
creator: False
bio:
With a passion for cybersecurity and a drive to learn and innovate, I am a Security Engineer at Innopolis University and a Cyber Security Engineer at Mossé Cyber Security Institute, where I apply my skills and knowledge in various domains of security, cloud, and automation. 

I have a Master's degree in Cybersecurity from Innopolis University, a Nanodegree in Cloud DevOps from Udacity, and a Bachelor of Engineering in Electrical and Electronics Engineering from the University of Benin. I am proficient in multiple technologies and tools, such as Azure Sentinel, AWS and Azure Cloud, Jenkins, CircleCI, Gitlab, Ansible, Terraform, Python, Bash, Docker, and Kubernetes. 

I have experience in network security engineering, SIEM, XDR, IDS/IPS, and endpoint security, and I have contributed to several projects that involved designing, implementing, and maintaining secure and scalable systems and solutions for clients and customers. I have also received multiple certifications in cybersecurity foundations, operationalizing MITRE ATT&CK, and ethical hacking from scratch. 

I am committed to performing and executing the assigned tasks while working in a fast-paced environment, and I am adept at identifying and researching the fastest and most effective ways to achieve the desired outcomes. I am also dedicated to staying current with industry developments and evolving technologies, and to leveraging my technical expertise and education to drive organizational growth and alleviate security concerns

name: Georgii Dzesov
headline: Senior Frontend Engineer
creator: False
bio:
With a Bachelor's in Computer Science from Innopolis University, I've honed my skills in JavaScript and Angular, currently applying them as a Senior Frontend Engineer at myTomorrows. Prior to this, I led a team at Tinkoff Bank, where we successfully developed and maintained a critical internal CRM system and various front-end libraries and APIs.

At Tinkoff Bank, our team's collaborative effort led to the CRM system handling the vast majority of client interactions, a testament to our commitment to excellence and innovation. We empowered each other through code reviews, mentorship, and the implementation of CI/CD, fostering a culture of continuous learning and improvement. By sharing diverse perspectives, we not only enhanced our internal processes but also contributed to a robust service delivery that aligns with our company values.

name: Alexander G.
headline: Data Analyst / ML-Engineer
creator: False
school_1: University of Belgrade, School of Electrical Engineering
bio:
As a data analyst at the bank, I carried out the downloading and analysis of data from the warehouse and BI system using queries, testing hypotheses, identifying anomalies, supporting reporting, generating technical specifications, and auditing the quality of execution. In another company I used Computer Vision and NLP technologies to parse resumes and key competencies of employees based on the description, and developed a recommendation system based on SVD and Factorization Machines. As a data-journalist I created a service for generating original texts for Internet articles and
extracting headlines, texts, and sources from data stories, integrating it with ML
Space API targeted at influential media agencies.

I have 2 years of development experience in the field of DS and AI and am open to any valuable offers! :)

I am also a computer science student at Innopolis University with a bachelor's degree. I have completed courses in applied machine learning, reinforcement learning, computer vision, natural language processing, applied AI, and more. I have participated in multiple hackathons, olympiads, schools, and conferences in Russia, Europe, and the CIS, where I have learned from and networked with experts and peers in the field. Additionally, I have experience as a data science intern at Innopolis University, where I created a deep learning model that measures student success in courses, and as a programming and computer science teacher at School 2035 / CDO "Small Academy of Sciences", where I mentor and tutor students in various topics and projects. I am open to any offers with the transition to full-time, as I am eager to apply my skills and knowledge to real-world problems and challenges.

bio:

While stadying in Innopolis I've got my skills in Networks, Linux administration and DevOps. In colaboration with Andrey Serebryakov we wrote our research project (https://drive.google.com/file/d/1oVnY48JLvWaYhxJxNY_qKHcfiZOJtz5p/view / https://www.researchgate.net/publication/347979581_Towards_a_Secure_and_Efficient_Location-based_Secret_Sharing_Protocol).

Hobby: Unity Engine, Raspberry, Arduino and other hardware fun, music composing.

bio:
[EN]
Experienced software engineer with over 2 years of experience in Python, Java, C, and more. I began my journey to understand how software works in 2013 and will continue to do so for the foreseeable future. I gained the majority of my knowledge by assisting friends and college students with various software engineering challenges.

Erfahrener Software-Ingenieur mit über 2 Jahren Erfahrung in Python, Java, C und mehr. Den größten Teil meines Wissens habe ich erworben, indem ich Freunden und Studenten bei verschiedenen Herausforderungen im Bereich der Softwaretechnik geholfen habe.

name: Vladimir Shcherba
location: St Petersburg, St Petersburg City, Russia
headline: Wild C++ developer from the town of Innopolis
creator: False
bio:
Starting from middle school, I became interested in programming and began participating in coding contests. I was learning GUI frameworks like Qt SDK and low-level 3D graphic libraries (like DirectX and OpenGL). Later on, I moved on to higher lever open-source game engines -- Oxygin, Urho3D and MOAI. Along with that I was reading some great books about software development, e. g. Code Complete, Patterns of Software Development, Game Engine Architecture, and so on, and applying gained skills in practice, writing small pet projects. While C++ was and still remains my primary language, I enjoyed learning other languages, like C, Python, or Rust.
Later I studied in the Innopolis University at Security and Network Engineering track, where I learned basics of security, cryptography, system administration and network programming, and also participated in a summer internship where I was leading a small team developing a VR game prototype in Unreal Engine 4.

Currently I work as a C++ backend developer . I am a developer of the Kagome project, the C++ implementation of a Polkadot Host. Also, for a hobby, I write pet-projects related to computer graphics programming and generic game development tools, mostly using Unreal Engine 4. 

My major interests are network programming, distributed systems, 3D rendering and low-level optimization. I also greatly enjoy sharing my knowledge by teaching in online schools and giving public talks.
